  "text": "The HTTP header sanitization/validation in envoy is implemented across three layers:\n\n1. **Header validation logic** (`header_utility.cc`): Core functions `requestHeadersValid()`, `headerNameIsValid()`, `headerValueIsValid()`, `checkHeaderNameForUnderscores()`, `checkValidRequestHeaders()`, and `authorityIsValid()` that validate header names/values against character tables and RFC rules. The UHV (Universal Header Validator) extensions in `source/extensions/http/header_validators/envoy_default/` provide protocol-specific validation via `validateRequestHeaders()`, `validateRequestHeaderEntry()`, `validateGenericHeaderName()`, `validateGenericHeaderValue()`, etc.\n\n2. **Forbidden header list enforcement** (`conn_manager_utility.cc::cleanInternalHeaders()`): Strips forbidden x-envoy-* internal headers from external/edge requests to prevent injection of trusted internal routing headers (retry, timeout, decorator, IP tags, etc.). Also removes route-config-specified `internalOnlyHeaders`.\n\n3. **Internal header stripping** (`conn_manager_utility.cc::mutateRequestHeaders()`): Removes Connection, Upgrade, KeepAlive, ProxyConnection, TransferEncoding, and EnvoyInternalRequest headers. Sanitizes the TE header and Referer header. The HTTP/1 and HTTP/2 codecs (`http1/codec_impl.cc`, `http2/codec_impl.cc`) perform additional per-header validation during parsing including underscore checks. `conn_manager_impl.cc` orchestrates the full pipeline: validates headers, normalizes paths/hosts, then calls `mutateRequestHeaders` which invokes `cleanInternalHeaders`.",
